<TITLE> 21 killed in Faridpur road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com)  At least 21 people, including three children, were killed and 40 injured as two buses collided on the Dhaka-Barisal highway in Faridpur on Sunday. The buses, a Gopalganj-bound Rajdhani Paribahan and Dhaka-bound Chandra Paribahan, crashed head-on at Koidubi Sadardi in Bhanga upazila at around 4.45pm. Local authorities said sixteen passengers of the two buses died on the spot. At least 40 passengers of both buses were injured. They were taken to nearby medical centres. Five in critical condition later succumbed to their injuries at Bhanga Upazila Health Complex, officials said. Deputy commissioner Helal Uddin said the bodies were being kept at Bhanga Police Station, while relatives were being traced. "The identification handover process is going on through the night," he said. Upazila Nirbahi Officer Shafikul Islam told bdnews24.com six bodies could be identified up to evening. Among them, three relatives of one surviving passenger 'Sagar', mother Mahfuza Begum, 30, three-year old sister and uncle Jamal, 24, were all killed in the accident. Sagar's severely injured father was admitted to hospital. The other three deceased who could be identified were Kamal Munshi, 30, a supervisor of Rajdhani Paribahan, and passengers 'Aman', 30, of Madaripur and Bibekando Boidyo, 65, from Gopalganj, The devastating accident created massive traffic tailbacks on the Dhaka-Barisal and Dhaka-Khulna highways, said police and rescue workers. bdnews24
